214
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:34,968
No.

215
00:19:39,055 --> 00:19:41,558
Why don't you come over here and sit?

216
00:19:59,409 --> 00:20:01,870
- You live here?
- I do now.

217
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,955
Because you're single?

218
00:20:04,539 --> 00:20:06,791
Who was your last boyfriend?

219
00:20:07,375 --> 00:20:08,627
My husband.

220
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:10,295
Was he English?

221
00:20:10,712 --> 00:20:13,340
- Very.
- What happened to him?

222
00:20:14,925 --> 00:20:16,551
Someone younger.

223
00:20:18,887 --> 00:20:21,765
You've got a great face.

224
00:20:22,974 --> 00:20:24,643
Doesn't everyone?

225
00:20:26,019 --> 00:20:27,520
I suppose so.

226
00:20:27,896 --> 00:20:28,939
I just...

227
00:20:29,022 --> 00:20:31,983
From the book,
somehow I thought you'd be less...

228
00:20:32,442 --> 00:20:33,610
What?

229
00:20:36,613 --> 00:20:38,782
I don't know what, exactly.

230
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:55,298
How do you feel about him using your life?

231
00:20:55,966 --> 00:20:58,426
It's really none of your business.

232
00:21:03,682 --> 00:21:06,142
When he let me in downstairs...

233
00:21:07,018 --> 00:21:08,687
he had this look.

234
00:21:11,106 --> 00:21:13,525
I just listened to your conversation.

235
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:20,198
I don't know what to say.

236
00:21:24,035 --> 00:21:25,870
I'm not a thief, Alice.

237
00:21:32,919 --> 00:21:34,004
Do you want a drink?

238
00:21:34,087 --> 00:21:36,590
I have some vodka in the fridge.
We could have a drink.

239
00:21:36,673 --> 00:21:38,508
Just take my picture.

240
00:21:59,654 --> 00:22:00,697
Good.

241
00:23:59,649 --> 00:24:00,734
Shit.

242
00:24:33,058 --> 00:24:34,893
